The Lowvelders were treated to an afternoon and evening of music, featuring several local bands before the South African band, Cutting Jade, took the stage at Blue Moon on Saturday March 26. The popular music venue opened its gates at 13:00, with several local bands performing to warm up the crowd for Cutting Jade’s live show at 20:00. The White River Swamp Rats, The Acoustics and DARE to Believe performed, and they soon had the audience dancing and headbanging in front of the stage. ALSO ERAD: Three men die in accident on N4 Toll Road towards Mbombela Cutting Jade took the stage, saying this show at Blue Moon was the first time they had performed in quite a while. Singing popular songs, such as “She Says” and “Lay You Down”, the band had gathered even more people to the front, dancing, jumping around and having a good time.  Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram